// src/pages/brands/smeg.astro
// Smeg brand pillar (Italian retro design, ~150-200 vol/mo aggregate across
// "Smeg appliance repair", "Smeg dishwasher repair", "Smeg oven repair" in
// LA-bias geo modifiers, KD 0). Built 2026-05-11. Tone reference:
// brands/marvel.astro pattern adapted to Smeg's design-first scope. Voice
// discipline: FAB-series retro refrigerator framing (the cream/red/pastel
// dome-top fridge that's the kitchen centerpiece in Silver Lake / Echo Park
// / Venice design-conscious households), 2015-2020 STA6047 dishwasher door
// latch assembly pattern at year 5-6, Smeg/Bertazzoni founding-family note
// (same Guastalla city, separate independent companies today), Italian
// parts lead-time reality (10-14 day typical), small-appliance scope
// honesty (we service major appliances only — not toasters/kettles/coffee).
//
// Pillar URL was clear of active redirect blocks (only a comment mention in
// astro.config.mjs at line 291 about residential-track routing for the
// /smeg-dishwasher-repair/ combo — no rule to remove). Direct write.

import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
import ServiceHero from '../../components/ServiceHero.astro';
import { MAIN_PHONE } from '../../data/branches';

const phone = MAIN_PHONE;
const phoneRaw = MAIN_PHONE.replace(/\D/g, '');
const phoneHref = `tel:+1${phoneRaw}`;
const canonical = "https://samedayappliance.repair/brands/smeg/";

const title = "Smeg Appliance Repair Los Angeles — Same Day";
const description = "Smeg dishwasher, oven, range & refrigerator repair in LA. Same-day service, OEM parts. Italian retro-design specialists. $89 diagnostic, waived with repair.";

const faqs = [
  {
    q: "What Smeg appliances do you repair in Los Angeles?",
    a: "Every major appliance Smeg sells in the US, across the dishwasher, range, refrigerator, wall oven, cooktop, and range-hood categories. Dishwashers (STA6047U, STU8612X, STA6249 — the ST/STA series accounts for the bulk of our Smeg service mix). Ranges (SF6991GPXE dual-fuel, SF4604WCNR portafino, the 24-inch and 30-inch and 36-inch gas and dual-fuel variants in the standard color palette plus the Italian-design specialty colors). Refrigerators (FAB28URRD1, FAB32, FAB50 — the iconic retro dome-top FAB series in 20-plus colors, plus the integrated column variants). Wall ovens (SF4604MCNX, SFP6604STPNR — single and double wall ovens, often paired with the FAB fridge in design-focused kitchens). Cooktops (PGF75X4 gas, the induction variants on the SI series). Range hoods (the integrated and decorative variants matching the range colorways). What we don't repair: Smeg small appliances — the toasters, kettles, stand mixers, coffee machines, blenders that are popular in LA design kitchens. Those route through Smeg's small-appliance service channel separately. We're a major-appliance service company; if it plugs into a 240V receptacle or a gas line, we service it. If it sits on a countertop, we don't."
  },
  {
    q: "How much does Smeg dishwasher repair cost in LA?",
    a: "Diagnostic is $89, applied toward the repair when you approve the work. Common Smeg dishwasher repairs: door latch assembly $245-$385 (the dominant STA6047 service item on the 2015-2020 production cohort — see year-pattern below); drain pump $245-$385; water inlet valve $185-$285; circulation pump $345-$525; control board $385-$525 (parts ship from Smeg USA distributor, 10-14 day typical lead for less-common items); door spring or hinge $185-$285; heating element $245-$385 (Smeg dishwashers use an in-circulation heater rather than a separate heating element on most US models, so this is a less common repair than on competing brands); detergent dispenser assembly $185-$285. Door gasket replacement runs $185-$285 — note that Smeg gaskets are specific to the model and color, not generic, so on colored-panel units (which is most of what we see) the gasket order routes through the US Smeg distributor specifically rather than aftermarket. We confirm parts availability and lead time at diagnostic before any work begins."
  },
  {
    q: "Can you repair my Smeg FAB retro refrigerator?",
    a: "Yes — and the FAB series is the Smeg product LA owners are most attached to. The FAB28, FAB32, and FAB50 dome-top retro refrigerators (available in 20-plus colors including the iconic cream, red, pastel green, pastel blue, and the seasonal Dolce & Gabbana collaboration patterns) anchor design-first kitchens across Silver Lake, Echo Park, Venice, West Hollywood, and the design corridors of Beverly Hills and Pacific Palisades. The FAB fridge is the kitchen centerpiece, not just an appliance — owners chose it for the look, paid the premium, and they want it repaired rather than replaced. We work around that mentality: repair-first quotes, OEM gaskets in the original color (not generic black), careful handling of the rounded-edge chrome trim. Common FAB service items: door gasket (color-matched, $245-$385 — these ship from the Smeg US distributor in the original color rather than aftermarket), evaporator fan motor ($245-$385), thermostat or thermistor ($185-$285), door hinge ($185-$285), control board ($385-$525), and on older units (year 12+) compressor work ($580-$880). Repair-vs-replace math on a FAB fridge tilts heavily toward repair — replacement units run $2,000-$2,800 and the owner usually doesn't want to lose the original color and finish."
  },
  {
    q: "Are Smeg and Bertazzoni the same company?",
    a: "Same founding family, separate companies today. Smeg was founded in 1948 in Guastalla, Italy, by Vittorio Bertazzoni — and yes, that's the same Bertazzoni family name that anchors the Bertazzoni cooking brand based in the same town. The two companies share the founding-family origin and the Guastalla, Italy heritage. They are independently owned and operated today, with distinct corporate structures, distinct US distribution networks, distinct product catalogs, and distinct parts channels. Practical service implication: if you have a Smeg dishwasher next to a Bertazzoni range in the same kitchen (a common configuration in Italian-design-focused LA homes), the parts and authorized service paths route separately even though both brands trace to the same founding family in the same town. We service both — same techs, same diagnostic visit if you have both brands, but the parts orders go through two separate US distributor channels. We track the Smeg/Bertazzoni distinction carefully because it routinely confuses customers and even some service companies."
  },
  {
    q: "Do you repair Smeg small appliances like toasters and kettles?",
    a: "No, we don't. The Smeg small-appliance line (the iconic 2-slot and 4-slot toasters, electric kettles, espresso machines, stand mixers, blenders, juicers, hand blenders) is popular in LA design kitchens as countertop accessories — they show up everywhere from Venice beach bungalows to Beverly Hills estates because the colorways match the FAB fridge and the brand identity. They're real Smeg products and they're real product investments. They are not, however, in our service scope. We're a major-appliance service company: anything that plugs into a 240V receptacle, runs on a gas line, or is built into the kitchen cabinetry. Countertop small appliances route through Smeg USA's small-appliance service channel separately — typically that's a mail-in or warranty-return process for the smaller items, and Smeg's customer service line handles the routing. If your Smeg toaster died, calling Smeg USA directly is the right path. If your Smeg dishwasher died, calling us is the right path."
  },
  {
    q: "How long do Smeg appliances last?",
    a: "Built for 12-15 year service life on the dishwashers and ranges, 15-20 years on the FAB refrigerator (the FAB is over-engineered for what it does — the dome chassis is built like a 1950s American refrigerator, which is part of the design point), and 10-12 years on the cooktops and wall ovens. Component wear is predictable: dishwasher door latch assembly at year 5-6 on the 2015-2020 STA6047 cohort, dishwasher drain pump at year 7-9 in high-use households, range igniters at year 6-8, FAB refrigerator door gaskets at year 6-8 (color UV-fade on the gasket exterior is a real factor in sun-exposed LA kitchens — coastal kitchens with afternoon western exposure see faster gasket service intervals), control boards at year 10-12 across the lineup. Repair-vs-replace math on Smeg almost always favors repair: dishwasher replacement runs $1,400-$2,200 against $200-$500 typical repair cost; FAB refrigerator replacement is $2,000-$2,800 and the owner is usually emotionally attached to the original color and finish; ranges run $3,000-$5,000 replacement against $300-$700 typical repair. We tell you the math at diagnostic but on Smeg specifically, the design-first ownership pattern means almost every customer wants the repair path through year 12-plus."
  },
  {
    q: "Where can I find the official Smeg manual or warranty information?",
    a: `Our technicians work independently of Smeg's factory service network — we're often faster and available same-day in Southern California.`
  }
];

const schemaJsons = [
  {
    "@context": "https://schema.org",
    "@type": "Service",
    "@id": canonical + "#service",
    "serviceType": "Smeg Appliance Repair",
    "name": "Smeg Appliance Repair, Same Day Appliance Repair",
    "url": canonical,
    "description": "Same-day Smeg dishwasher, range, refrigerator, wall oven, cooktop, and range-hood repair across Los Angeles, Orange, Ventura, San Bernardino, and Riverside counties. FAB retro refrigerators (FAB28URRD1, FAB32, FAB50 — 20-plus colors including Dolce & Gabbana collaboration variants), ST/STA dishwashers (STA6047U, STU8612X), SF dual-fuel and gas ranges (SF6991GPXE, SF4604WCNR — 24/30/36-inch variants), SF4604MCNX wall ovens, PGF75X4 gas cooktops, SI induction cooktops. Factory-trained on Smeg-specific service patterns: 2015-2020 STA6047 dishwasher door latch wear, FAB refrigerator color-matched gasket service (OEM-only, not aftermarket), Smeg/Bertazzoni founding-family distinction (same Guastalla origin, separate companies today). Major-appliance scope only — Smeg small appliances (toasters, kettles, coffee, mixers) route through Smeg USA separately. $89 residential diagnostic, applied toward repair.",
    "provider": {
      "@type": "LocalBusiness",
