/>

<!-- 01 INTRO -->
<section class="section">
  <div class="container narrow">
    <p class="section-number">01, About this service</p>
    <h2 class="section-title">Smeg is Italian retro — and in LA we see them in Silver Lake, West Hollywood, Venice, and Echo Park kitchens where the FAB fridge or the cream-colored range is the centerpiece of the kitchen, not just an appliance.</h2>

    <p>The Smeg story in our LA service mix is design-first ownership. The iconic FAB28 dome-top refrigerator in cream, the FAB32 in pastel mint, the SF6991GPXE 30-inch dual-fuel range in classic red — these aren't appliances people chose because they were the best dishwasher or the most efficient fridge on the spec sheet. They were chosen because they look right in a Silver Lake mid-century renovation, in a Venice beach bungalow with terrazzo floors, in an Echo Park hillside kitchen with vintage tile. Our typical Smeg customer is design-aware, repair-first by mentality, and emotionally attached to the original finish on their appliance. We work around that reality: repair-first quotes, OEM color-matched parts (gaskets specifically — Smeg gaskets ship in the original color from the US distributor, not generic black), careful handling of chrome trim and rounded-edge design elements, honest math on repair-vs-replace that almost always lands on repair through year 12-plus.</p>

    <p>Two Smeg-specific realities shape every service call we run. First, <strong>Smeg parts ship from the US Smeg distributor with typical 10-14 day lead time</strong> on less-common items. The brand maintains a US distribution network, but the parts pipeline reaches back to Guastalla, Italy, for items the US distributor doesn't stock domestically — and that means longer lead time than mass-market brands. We confirm parts availability and timing at diagnostic before quoting, and we keep common Smeg wear items (door latch assemblies for the STA dishwasher series, igniters for the SF ranges, common gaskets in the dominant colors) on the truck for same-day completion when symptoms can be identified by phone. Second, <strong>Smeg and Bertazzoni share founding-family origin but are separate companies</strong>. Vittorio Bertazzoni founded Smeg in 1948 in Guastalla, Italy — the same Bertazzoni family name that anchors the Bertazzoni cooking brand based in the same town. The two companies are independently owned and operated today, with distinct US distribution networks and distinct parts channels. We track this distinction carefully because it confuses both customers and some service companies.</p>

    <p>This page covers Smeg repair across the major-appliance lineup. Every Smeg service call gets a $89 residential diagnostic (applied toward the repair when work is approved), OEM Smeg parts via the US distributor network, and an honest written quote with parts lead-time disclosed before any work begins. Smeg small appliances (toasters, kettles, coffee machines, stand mixers, blenders) are not in our scope — those route through Smeg USA's small-appliance service channel separately.</p>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- 02 DISHWASHERS -->
<section class="section section-gray">
  <div class="container">
    <p class="section-number">02, Smeg dishwashers — the dominant category in our service mix</p>
    <h2 class="section-title">ST/STA series dishwashers, and the 2015-2020 STA6047 door latch pattern.</h2>

    <p class="lead">Smeg dishwashers (ST/STA series, plus the integrated panel-ready variants) account for the largest share of our Smeg service work. The STA6047U is the dominant model on our route — fully-integrated, panel-ready, 24-inch built-in, popular in custom kitchens across the Westside and the design-conscious neighborhoods of East LA.</p>

    <div class="callout-box">
      <h3>2015-2020 STA6047 door latch assembly pattern (the most common Smeg service call in LA)</h3>
      <p>The STA6047U and surrounding STA-series production years between roughly 2015 and 2020 develop a consistent door latch assembly failure around year 5 to 6. Symptoms: dishwasher won't start when door is closed (latch isn't engaging the door-closed switch), or starts but stops mid-cycle when the door registers as open, or won't lock during the wash cycle. The latch assembly's internal microswitch fatigues from the high cycle count common in LA households (the design demographic that buys Smeg tends to run the dishwasher daily or more). <strong>Replacement runs $245-$385, often same-day when we stock the common STA latch assemblies on the truck.</strong> Worth checking the door hinge and door spring at the same visit — when the latch is wearing this fast, the door geometry has often drifted slightly and a $35-$60 hinge adjustment at the same visit prolongs the new latch's service life.</p>
    </div>

    <p>Beyond the latch pattern, Smeg dishwasher service tree covers a predictable set of items:</p>

    <ul class="bullet-list">
      <li><strong>Year 3-5:</strong> Detergent dispenser assembly on heavily-used units ($185-$285), water inlet valve ($185-$285).</li>
      <li><strong>Year 5-6:</strong> Door latch assembly (above) — the dominant STA-series service item.</li>
      <li><strong>Year 7-9:</strong> Drain pump ($245-$385 — common in high-use design-aware households running the dishwasher daily), circulation pump ($345-$525), door gasket ($185-$285, color-specific not generic).</li>
      <li><strong>Year 10-12:</strong> Control board ($385-$525), heating element on units that have a separate heater rather than in-circulation heat ($245-$385), door spring or hinge full replacement ($245-$385).</li>
    </ul>

    <p>The Smeg dishwasher service profile is design-bias forward: customers want the unit fixed rather than replaced because Smeg dishwashers are integrated into custom panel-ready cabinetry in most of these installations, and replacement means re-cutting the cabinet panel to match a different unit's dimensions. We respect that constraint in quoting — through year 12, repair almost always wins the math on a Smeg dishwasher, and we walk through it carefully when the quote approaches $500.</p>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- 03 REFRIGERATORS, RANGES, WALL OVENS, COOKTOPS -->
<section class="section">
  <div class="container">
    <p class="section-number">03, FAB refrigerators, SF ranges, wall ovens, cooktops</p>
    <h2 class="section-title">The rest of the Smeg lineup — and the FAB fridge that LA owners are most attached to.</h2>

    <p class="lead">Beyond dishwashers, Smeg's US major-appliance lineup covers the iconic FAB retro refrigerators, SF dual-fuel and gas ranges, SF wall ovens, PGF and SI cooktops, and the integrated range hoods that match the range colorways. Each category has its own service profile but shares the underlying Smeg engineering platform and the design-first ownership pattern.</p>

    <div class="appliance-grid">
      <div class="appliance-card">
        <h3>FAB retro refrigerators (FAB28 / FAB32 / FAB50)</h3>
        <p>The iconic dome-top retro refrigerator in 20-plus colors including cream, red, pastel green, pastel blue, plus the seasonal Dolce & Gabbana collaboration patterns. Service items: door gasket (color-matched OEM, not generic — $245-$385), evaporator fan motor ($245-$385), thermostat / thermistor ($185-$285), door hinge ($185-$285), control board ($385-$525). Year 12-plus: compressor work ($580-$880). LA owners are emotionally attached to the original color — repair-vs-replace tilts heavily toward repair.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="appliance-card">
        <h3>SF series dual-fuel and gas ranges</h3>
        <p>SF6991GPXE 30-inch dual-fuel, SF4604WCNR 36-inch portafino, and the 24-inch / 30-inch / 36-inch variants in standard and specialty colors. Service items: surface igniter ($185-$245 per burner — common at year 6-8), oven igniter ($245-$385), bake element on electric-side variants ($245-$385), oven temperature sensor ($185-$245), control board ($385-$525), gas valve ($245-$385). Smeg ranges run reliably through year 10-12 with normal service.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="appliance-card">
        <h3>SF wall ovens (SF4604MCNX, SFP6604STPNR)</h3>
        <p>Single and double 24-inch and 30-inch wall ovens, often paired with the FAB fridge in design-focused kitchen installations. Service items: oven igniter, bake element, oven temperature sensor, fan motor (convection variants), control board. Service profile similar to SF ranges — year 10-12 typical service life with normal use.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="appliance-card">
        <h3>Cooktops (PGF gas, SI induction)</h3>
        <p>PGF75X4 30-inch gas cooktop (5-burner, the most common Smeg cooktop on our route), 36-inch gas variants, SI induction cooktops. Service items: surface igniter, gas valve, induction coil on the SI series (less common but real on year 8-plus units), control board. Induction service requires the SI-specific replacement coil — 10-14 day lead from the Smeg US distributor.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="appliance-card">
        <h3>Range hoods (integrated and decorative)</h3>
        <p>Smeg ventilation paired with the SF ranges in matching colorways. Service items: motor, light assembly, control board, filter retention. Less common in our Smeg service mix than the dishwasher and FAB categories, but real and recurring.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="appliance-card">
        <h3>Honest scope — what we don't service</h3>
        <p>Smeg small appliances — toasters, kettles, espresso machines, stand mixers, blenders, juicers, hand blenders. These are popular in LA design kitchens as countertop accessories but they're not in our service scope. They route through Smeg USA's small-appliance service channel separately. We're a major-appliance service company; if it sits on a countertop and plugs into a standard 120V outlet, we don't service it.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- 04 MODELS -->
<section class="section section-gray">
  <div class="container">
    <p class="section-number">04, Models we service most often</p>
    <h2 class="section-title">Smeg model families in heavy SoCal service rotation.</h2>

    <p class="lead">A representative sample of Smeg model families our techs service routinely. Not exhaustive — Smeg's US catalog covers more variants — but covers the units that show up most often on our route.</p>

    <div class="model-grid">
      <div class="model-card">
        <h3>Dishwashers (ST/STA series)</h3>
        <p class="model-list">STA6047U · STU8612X · STA6249 · STFABUWH</p>
        <p>Fully-integrated, panel-ready, and the FAB-styled freestanding variant. The 2015-2020 STA6047 cohort is the door latch pattern. Built-in panel-ready dominates the LA install base.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="model-card">
        <h3>FAB Refrigerators</h3>
        <p class="model-list">FAB28URRD1 · FAB32 · FAB50 · FAB30LCR</p>
        <p>The iconic dome-top retro fridge. 20-plus colors. FAB28 is the 24-inch model, FAB32 is the 28-inch, FAB50 is the 50-inch French-door variant. Color-matched gaskets ship via the US Smeg distributor.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="model-card">
        <h3>Ranges (SF series)</h3>
        <p class="model-list">SF6991GPXE · SF4604WCNR · SF6604WTPNR · SFPR9606WTPNR</p>
        <p>30-inch and 36-inch dual-fuel and all-gas ranges. Standard color palette plus Italian-design specialty colors. Surface igniters are the common year 6-8 service item.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="model-card">
        <h3>Wall Ovens (SF series)</h3>
        <p class="model-list">SF4604MCNX · SFP6604STPNR · SF6604WTPNR</p>
        <p>24-inch and 30-inch single and double wall ovens. Convection variants on the higher-end models. Common service items: igniter, bake element, temperature sensor.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="model-card">
        <h3>Cooktops (PGF gas, SI induction)</h3>
        <p class="model-list">PGF75X4 · PGF36U · SI964 · SIM61MBL</p>
        <p>30-inch and 36-inch gas cooktops, 24-inch and 30-inch induction. Induction coil replacement on SI-series requires 10-14 day lead from the US distributor.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="model-card">
        <h3>Range Hoods</h3>
        <p class="model-list">KSEG90X · KT70 · KSGT75X · KE91</p>
        <p>Wall-mount, under-cabinet, and island ventilation matching the SF range colorways. Service items: motor, light assembly, control board, filter retention.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- 05 PRICING -->
<section class="section">
  <div class="container">
    <p class="section-number">05, Pricing</p>
    <h2 class="section-title">What Smeg appliance repair costs in Southern California.</h2>

    <p class="lead">Diagnostic is $89, applied toward the repair when you approve the work. Smeg pricing sits in the mid-luxury repair tier — parts ship from the US Smeg distributor, typical 10-14 day lead for less-common items, common wear parts (STA dishwasher door latch assemblies, FAB gaskets in dominant colors, SF range igniters) on the truck for same-day completion.</p>

    <div class="pricing-grid">
      <div class="price-card">
        <div class="price-label">Diagnostic</div>
        <div class="price-amount">$89</div>
        <div class="price-desc">Waived when you approve repair</div>
      </div>
      <div class="price-card">
        <div class="price-label">Standard band</div>
        <div class="price-amount">$145–$385</div>
        <div class="price-desc">Door latch · igniter · water inlet · door gasket · thermostat</div>
      </div>
      <div class="price-card">
        <div class="price-label">Major component</div>
        <div class="price-amount">$285–$525</div>
        <div class="price-desc">Drain pump · circulation pump · evaporator fan · control board · induction coil</div>
      </div>
      <div class="price-card">
        <div class="price-label">Compressor / sealed-system</div>
        <div class="price-amount">$580–$880</div>
        <div class="price-desc">FAB refrigerator compressor swap on year 12-plus units · refrigerant work</div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <p class="price-note">Repair-vs-replace math on Smeg almost always favors repair. Replacement-unit pricing: dishwasher $1,400-$2,200; FAB refrigerator $2,000-$2,800 (and the original color often isn't in stock); range $3,000-$5,000; wall oven $2,500-$3,800; cooktop $1,500-$2,800. Against typical repair costs of $200-$500 on most service items, repair wins the math through year 12-plus on every category. The design-first ownership pattern compounds it — Smeg customers chose the brand for the look and they want to keep it. We tell you the math at diagnostic so you can decide, but the math almost always lands on repair.</p>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- 06 RECENT REPAIRS -->
<section class="section section-gray">
  <div class="container">
    <p class="section-number">06, Recent repairs</p>
    <h2 class="section-title">Smeg jobs from across the territory.</h2>

