        <h3>Smeg STA6047U dishwasher, Silver Lake</h3>
        <p><strong>Symptom:</strong> Owner reported the dishwasher wouldn't start. Door closed normally, panel lights came on, but pressing START produced no response. Issue had developed gradually over a week — first intermittent, then total. Unit was 6 years old in a 2018 Silver Lake hillside remodel.</p>
        <p><strong>Diagnosis:</strong> Classic 2015-2020 STA6047 door latch assembly failure pattern. Internal microswitch fatigued, not registering the door-closed signal. Door hinge geometry also checked — slight drift but within tolerance, no replacement needed.</p>
        <p><strong>Repair:</strong> Door latch assembly replacement with OEM Smeg part (in stock on truck — common STA item). Hinge adjustment at the same visit (no charge — preventive). Verified normal start sequence and full wash cycle.</p>
        <p><strong>Cost & time:</strong> $285 total (latch only). Same-day, 75 minutes on-site.</p>
