        <p><strong>Symptom:</strong> Owner reported the front-left surface burner igniter clicking but not igniting — burner working fine if lit manually but auto-ignition had stopped. Other 4 burners igniting normally. Unit was 7 years old in a Norma Triangle condo, classic cream color.</p>
        <p><strong>Diagnosis:</strong> Year 7 surface igniter failure — well within the standard SF-series wear window. Igniter spark gap eroded from accumulated cooking grease deposits and normal cycle wear. Single-burner repair, no other items needed.</p>
        <p><strong>Repair:</strong> Surface igniter replacement with OEM Smeg part (in stock on truck — common SF igniter). Verified auto-ignition across all 5 burners and normal operation. Customer also asked about oven igniter — tested clean, no replacement needed at this visit.</p>
        <p><strong>Cost & time:</strong> $225 total. Same-day, 45 minutes on-site.</p>
